name: Google Drive
description: Add a Google Drive Instance to connect your existing Google Drive account to the Cloud Storage and Documents Hub, allowing you to manage files and folders. You will need your Google Drive account information to add an instance.
configDescription: If you do not have an Google Drive account, you can create one at Google Drive Signup

configuration.name: Refresh Interval
configuration.description: Google Drive user refresh token Interval

configuration.name: Last Event Change ID
configuration.description: The last event change ID retrieved

configuration.name: Base URL
configuration.description: The Base URL to make API requests to this endpoint

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Document Hub Tagging
configuration.description: Enable Tagging of Documents. Paths and Tags will be stored in CE database in Clear Text

configuration.name: Event Notification Subscription ID
configuration.description: The subscription ID for the webhook events subscription

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Revoke Access Token
configuration.description: Whether to revoke the access token while deleting the instance

configuration.name: Include TeamDrives For All Calls
configuration.description: A Key used to generate includeTeamDrives for all calls

configuration.name: Custom URL for Webhooks That is registered with Google
configuration.description: Custom URL for Webhooks That is registered with Google

configuration.name: Google Drive Poller Page Token
configuration.description: Google Drive Event Poller Page Token.

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Set time interval for polling application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Resources Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. The configuration is defined via JSON, an example of which is as follows - { "documents": { "url": "/hubs/docuemnts/documents"} }

configuration.name: Event Notification Callback URL
configuration.description: An application callback URL used for event notifications from Google Drive via Cloud Elements

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

resources.description: Deletes a file from your cloud service by its specified path.

parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt)

parameters.description: Defaults to true, when set to false the filename will not be used and a random file name will be generated while downloading

resources.description: Retrieves a single file from your cloud service from a specified path. The file is directly streamed from the cloud storage provider through Cloud Elements, and is not buffered to disk.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt)

parameters.name: includeTeamDrives
parameters.description: Whether Team Drive items should be included in results. Defaults to false

parameters.name: teamDriveId
parameters.description: The teamdrive ID. This ID is required if contents need to be listed from a specific teamdrive

parameters.name: mediaType
parameters.description: Optional mediaType as defined by the google sdk to send for conversion for google docs. By default Documents are converted to MS Word, Presentation are converted to MS Powerpoint, and SpreadSheets are converted to MS Excel. You can override this default behavior by supplying your own conversion.

resources.description: Uploads a file to your endpoint cloud service. If the destination path includes directories that do not exist, they will be created.

parameters.name: file
parameters.description: The file to be uploaded

parameters.name: thumbnail
parameters.description: The thumbnail for the file to be set

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the file (e.g. /myDirectory/myFile.txt). If folderId is also given, then path will be ignored and the file will be saved in the folder pointing to the given folderId.

parameters.name: folderId
parameters.description: The folder id is where the file should be uploaded to, this is required when calculateFolderPath is set to false. If calculateFolderPath is set to true and folderId is provided, then the folderId will be ignored. folderId is of higher priority, so if the path parameter is also provided, then it will be ignored.

parameters.name: mimeType
parameters.description: The mimeType of the file. (e.g. text/plain).

parameters.name: size
parameters.description: The size of the file in bytes (required only for SharePoint)

parameters.name: tags[]
parameters.description: Tags associated with the file

parameters.name: description
parameters.description: Description of the file

parameters.name: overwrite
parameters.description: Overwrite the file if the file exists

parameters.name: calculateFolderPath
parameters.description: Whether or not to construct the path for each item in the response. Defaults to true, when set to false folderId is required

resources.description: Update a file's metadata (tags and path) associated with an ID.  For example, if you had a document that was tagged as operations but needed to be tagged as legal, then you would perform a PATCH to update the tag using the tags JSON array field. resources.description: Get a list of CloudFiles that are contained in a specified folder on your cloud service specified by a path.

parameters.name: includeTeamDrives
parameters.description: Whether Team Drive items should be included in results. Defaults to false

parameters.description: The teamdrive ID. This ID is required if contents need to be listed from a specific teamdrive

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. When this field is left blank all files & folders in the specified directory will be returned. If you want only subdirectories in a directory, directory='true'. To search for specific file with name myFile.txt, name='myFile.txt'. To get subdirectories along with file search, name='myFile.txt' OR directory ='true'. Expressions LIKE & IN are also supported - eg. extension IN ('txt','png'), name LIKE 'file_name'. In the case that a file does not have an extension try filtering on mimeType.

parameters.name: orderBy
parameters.description: Defines the order of the data using following keys createdDate, modifiedDate, name. (Default value of createdDate desc). For instance createdDate asc / name asc, createdDate desc

parameters.name: fetchTags
parameters.description: Whether or not to return the tags for the files in the folder

parameters.name: calculateFolderPath
parameters.description: Calculate the folder path. Defaults to true

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

Performs a text search of file names and directory names.  The content of files is not searched.  The search uses substring matching so searching for "exam" will match on "example.txt".  Subdirectories are also searched.  The search returns a list of CloudFiles that match search parameters.

parameters.name: path
parameters.description: The full path to the folder to start searching from (e.g. /myDirectory)

parameters.name: text
parameters.description: Text in the file or folder name

parameters.name: orderBy
parameters.description: Defines the order of the data using following keys createdDate, modifiedDate, name. (Default value of createdDate desc). For instance createdDate asc / name asc, createdDate desc

parameters.name: calculateFolderPath
parameters.description: Calculate the folder path. By default, the Google Drive API does not support folder paths. The default value of this flag is 'true', if false, it will only search the root directory. Note: The Google Drive API may timeout if the provided search text is not specific enough.

parameters.name: startDate
parameters.description: The start date (based on the created date of the file or folder) if used, end date is required

parameters.name: endDate
parameters.description: The end date (based on the created date of the file or folder) if used, start date is required

parameters.name: tags[]
parameters.description: Any tags associated with the files (not applicable to folders)

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied
